    <text>
        <div>
            <head>Translated parts</head>
            <p xml:id="CH1a0940-start">
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-7a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T20:42:39.441+09:00">the true gentleman will not exercise
                    that ability.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-7a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T20:46:30.797+09:00">It is not as if the true gentleman
                    takes pleasure in speaking up</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T22:54:47.459+09:00">As for naming it is what properly sorts
                    out shapes.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T21:55:09.893+09:00">If the sorting out of shapes comes from
                    names</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:20:07.356+09:00">then naming must not deviate from what
                    is accurate (正).</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:30:25.33+09:00">If one governs in accordance with the
                    Supreme Way</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:12:08.092+09:00">then disputers, legalists, Confucians,
                    Mohists disappear of themselves;</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:13:29.825+09:00">and if one governs in accordance with
                    disputers, legalists, Confucians, and Mohists</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:18:41.104+09:00">then one still has no chance of getting
                    away from the Way.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:27:50.449+09:00">it is the treasure of the good,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-11T23:32:58.863+09:00">Those who govern in accordance with the
                    Way</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:14:09.569+09:00">their names and their lot in life
                    becoming more distant from each other day by day</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-17a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-12T21:31:55.521+09:00">直解：29:人君承接萬物，必劃分而區別之。使之各安其分。</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-17a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-12T22:02:31.805+09:00">they all tried to draw it and gave up
                    half way through.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_002-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-13T20:47:21.646+09:00">if the relations of above and</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_002-11a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T03:00:26.191+09:00">so that</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_002-12a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T03:13:01.188+09:00">so</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-17T17:30:34.223+09:00">should/must have a name, (see 形而不名
                    below.)</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:00:45.623+09:00">If something is shaped but one has not
                    named it (given it a name)</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:06:25.019+09:00">one absolutely has to find out about
                    the name in order to ascertain the distinction made.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T22:55:31.344+09:00">For referring to (concrete) matters
                    there is naming.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T22:56:48.363+09:00">The Greatest Way has no shape (that
                    would allow one to name it).</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:16:06.807+09:00">And so Confucius has it:</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:16:09.747+09:00">"What is necessary is sorting out
                    properly the naming.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:30:41.638+09:00">When the naming is not properly sorted
                    out</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:31:26.271+09:00">then language will not follow the
                    norms."</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:35:53.663+09:00">The Great Way is not referred to by
                    name,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:37:21.485+09:00">while all existing beings must be
                    named,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:38:11.326+09:00">but these arise from what is not
                    referred to by name</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:41:41.436+09:00">so that all the shapes of things
                    naturally get their concrete physical properties.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:41:30.897+09:00">Naming arises from concrete physical
                    properties.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-14T23:43:56.991+09:00">so that all names get to have that to
                    which they refer by name.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:15:46.754+09:00">"The Way is the holiest of the holies
                    of all things;</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:09:04.927+09:00">and it is what those who are not good
                    (also!) treasure.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:11:12.44+09:00">one calls "the good people",</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:11:47.132+09:00">and those who govern in accordance with
                    sophism, legalism, Confucianism, and Mohism</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:12:27.012+09:00">these one calls "the not good
                    people".</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:13:44.338+09:00">As for the good people and the not good
                    people,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:15:18.606+09:00">one can get to understand without
                    having to make a meticulous study of it.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T00:15:34.758+09:00">Laozi said:</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T02:36:44.519+09:00"/>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T02:37:43.914+09:00">but that which has a name need not have
                    a physical shape.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-17T17:30:38.387+09:00">it does not necessarily fail to have
                    the concrete realities of squareness/roundness or whiteness/blackness.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:04:04.178+09:00">read: 名而不可不尋名...But when one names
                    it</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:10:29.181+09:00">Therefore there are also namings with
                    the purpose of investigating shapes.</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:12:33.228+09:00">and shapes serving to define
                    namings;</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:13:25.683+09:00">naming may serve to define
                    situations,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:14:04.531+09:00">and situations may help to investigate
                    names,</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T03:15:39.394+09:00">so that the relation between shapes and
                    names as well as situations and things</seg>
                <seg corresp="#CH1a0940_CHANT_001-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2020-04-15T04:42:52.108+09:00">will have nowhere to hide its
                    undelrying pattern (i.e. will be quite clear).</seg>
            </p>
        </div>
